#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:13
msgid "How to fading in-out Kdenlive titles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:15
msgid "In this short *HOWTO* video, we show you how to (smoothly) fade in and out Kdenlive titles over a video clip, fading from and to transparency. The key to success is to use a **Composite & Transform** transition with keyframes (**Affine** and **Composite** will work too). **Don’t use** the Fade from/to Black effects though, as these effects remove the title transparency information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:23
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""
"Нотатки"

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:25
msgid "These are the individual steps shown in this HOWTO video:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:27
msgid "Add a Composite & Transform transition to the title clip."
msgstr ""

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:28
msgid "First keyframe: set the opacity to 0%. This marks the beginning of the fade in (ramp up)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:30
msgid "Second keyframe: add a new keyframe where you want the title to be fully faded in, set the opacity to 100%. Set the type of the keyframe to Linear."
msgstr ""

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:30
msgid "The rationale to set this keyframe to Linear is that otherwise Kdenlive (MLT) calculates a smooth curve fitting to the previous and following keyframe, causing the opacity value to overshoot. With a maximum possible opacity of 100% you won’t notice. However, when you use a maximum opacity of less than 100%, then this overshooting may become visible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:31
msgid "Ensure that the first keyframe is Smooth. You can only adjust the type of the first keyframes after you’ve added a second keyframe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:32
msgid "Third keyframe: add another keyframe near the end where you want to start fading out the title. Leave the opacity at 100%. Set the keyframe type to Smooth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:33
msgid "Fourth keyframe: add a final keyframe, where you set the opacity to 0%."
msgstr ""

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:35
msgid "Done."
msgstr ""
"Готово."

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/howto_fading_inout_kdenlive_titles.rst:37
msgid "In case you are scratching your head now, why this mixture of smooth and linear interpolated keyframes? Then head over to our new article on :ref:`the_smooth_keyframe_interpolation`."
msgstr ""
